<br>
Now about these stats, it's real simple. What I'm about to say are fact, not opinion. EQ is a computer game and is therefore grounded in absolutes. The following are absolute truths.<br>
<br>
1)no stat increases your chance to dodge/parry/riposte. It's a random roll based off your skill level every time a mob hits you.<br>
2)Wis/Int both increase the chances of doing trade skills. Whichever one is higher is the one that is applied. There is no difference between having them both at 200 and only having one at 200. Also, for certain trade skills (like blacksmithing) there are other attributes that can take the place of wis/int (such as str in the case of blacksmithing).<br>
3)Dex directly effects how often you crit and how often you proc. Every time you connect a die is rolled that does a check based on what your dex is at (since there is no crit or proc skill). <br>
<br>
Those are true. If you argue with me, you are wrong, because I'm right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Now about the dex thing. First off, you will probably almost never have boon on you. Secondly, you will very rarely have visions of granduer on you since most chanters that high will just shissar you anyways. And dex is VERY important once you get your epic because every proc off that thing is 500 hate. The more it procs, the better you hold your aggro. But on the other side, you can stack dex buffs with Focus, so you can actually get your dex nice and high during raids. I never plan my char that way though. I don't want to have to rely on others to make my stats what they should be. <p>Shelrabbi Hassida<BR>
Tallon Zek<BR>
